The paper proposes a hybrid metaheuristic to solve two optimisation problems related to city logistics and transportation systems. The approach combines enumerative local searches with destroy-and-repair principles and tailored operators. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) due to the use of metaheuristics. Additionally, the paper deals with routing problems, which could place it in the sub-categories of robotics (cs.RO) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper addresses issues related to city logistics and transportation systems, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
